# Coding Standards

## 1. Variable Naming — No Short Meaningless Names

All variable, parameter, and function names must be at least 4 characters and descriptive.

```typescript
// BAD
const s = 'hello';
const cb = () => {};
items.map((e) => e.name);
const d = new Date();
const i = 0;
const r = rows[0];
const comp = 'CNV UI';
const val = draft[key];
const sys = data.system;

// GOOD
const message = 'hello';
const callback = () => {};
items.map((item) => item.name);
const date = new Date();
const index = 0;
const firstRow = rows[0];
const component = 'CNV UI';
const settingValue = draft[key];
const systemInfo = data.system;
```

Single-letter exceptions allowed ONLY in:
- Generic type parameters: `<T>`, `<K, V>`
- Unused event params required by API: `(_event, value) =>`

## 2. Arrow Functions Only

Use arrow functions for all declarations. The `function` keyword is only allowed when `this` binding is required (e.g., class methods, Mocha-style tests).

```typescript
// BAD
function calculateRate(total, passed) { ... }
function MyComponent() { ... }

// GOOD
const calculateRate = (total: number, passed: number) => { ... };
const MyComponent: React.FC = () => { ... };
```

React components should use `const Name: React.FC = () => (...)`.

## 3. No Inline Styling

All styles must be in CSS files. Do not use the `style` prop on JSX elements.

```tsx
// BAD
<div style={{ marginTop: 16, color: 'red' }}>text</div>
<input style={{ padding: '4px', border: '1px solid var(...)' }} />

// GOOD — use CSS classes
<div className="app-mt-md app-text-danger">text</div>
<input className="app-time-input" />
```

Add classes to `packages/client/src/styles/app.css` using PatternFly CSS variables for consistency.

## 4. File Length — Max 300 Lines

No single file should exceed **300 lines**. If a file grows beyond this:

- **Pages**: Extract sections into sub-components (e.g., `SettingsPage` → `ReportPortalSettings`, `NotificationSubscriptions`)
- **Store files**: Split by domain (e.g., `store.ts` → `store/launches.ts`, `store/subscriptions.ts`)
- **Components**: Extract complex logic into custom hooks
- **API files**: Split by resource if too many functions

```
// BAD — 900-line SettingsPage.tsx with 8 sections
SettingsPage.tsx (900 lines)

// GOOD — split into focused components
SettingsPage.tsx (150 lines) — layout + section composition
  components/settings/ReportPortalSettings.tsx (80 lines)
  components/settings/JiraSettings.tsx (90 lines)
  components/settings/NotificationSubscriptions.tsx (120 lines)
  components/settings/UserManagement.tsx (80 lines)
```

## 5. Constants and Magic Values

No magic numbers or strings in JSX or logic. Extract to named constants.

```typescript
// BAD
if (days <= 7) return 'warning';
staleTime: 300000

// GOOD
const WARNING_THRESHOLD_DAYS = 7;
if (days <= WARNING_THRESHOLD_DAYS) return 'warning';

const FIVE_MINUTES_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;
staleTime: FIVE_MINUTES_MS
```
